content:
**Lower bound:** r̂ > n² + 0.577·n^{3/2}

This exceeds the conjectured C(2n+1,2) - C(n,2) ≈ n² + n for large n.

The gap of Θ(n^{3/2}) disproves the conjecture.

The gap between Pikhurko's bounds:

(√2 - 0.577)·n^{3/2} + n ≈ 0.84·n^{3/2}

This gap grows as n^{3/2}, so the relative error shrinks as n → ∞, but the absolute error grows.
